data.text: Duke University is a Christian privately funded research university located in Durham, North Carolina. The university owns 256 buildings, and its campus grounds are split up into four main areas: East, West, Central, and the Medical Center. Among these, West campus is considered the main campus as the majority of the university’s academic and administrative centers are situated within it. Additionally, Duke and the National University of Singapore have a formal collaboration project in the Duke-NUS Medical School in Singapore.
